atter of magnitude  To give you a sense  it used to be that people who  say you are in charge of awarding contracts and so one and somebody bids for it you might cut some deal with someone to get 10 percent and that was viewed as a horrible thing  And then 10 percent went to maybe like 20 and 30  What has happened right now  which almost no Nigerian finds acceptable    an example will be somebody who holds office has a business partner that he favors and awards a contract maybe for a bridge  100 percent of the money for the bridge will be paid out and there will be no bridge  None  Certain rivers have had three or four bridges built across them that have never existed in reality  That s the current state  And even for Nigerians  that is too much  Which is why  Muhammadu  Buhari   is out there  Remember  a lot of the folks in the southwest are Christians  Buhari s running mate is an associate pastor of the Redeemed Church of Nigeria  OK  Buhari  when he went to Lagos a couple of months ago  laid out this challenge to Jonathan and every other Nigerian politician out there  He said   I was a military general and a head of state  I challenge anyone to bring to public any contracts that I may have given to myself or to anybody thought to be fronting for me  He said   I have no single foreign bank accounts  None  If you associate any bank account to my name that is not Nigerian  I beg you to bring it forth  He said   I have two houses  one in Kaduna and one in Fantora  I don t have a plot in Abuja  the Nigerian capital  I don t a house in Abuja  He said   If you of anything  bring it forth  No other Nigerian politician who has had opportunity   he was minister of petroleum  he was military president of Nigeria  he was the chair of the petroleum trust fund which was a fund created to use resources from petroleum for capital projects such as roads and big buildings and so forth  And he built roads  This is on record  Nigerians know this  So the only thing if you look at Jon